U-Net & ANTsR intro

The current version of the multilabel_dice_coefficient function does not work with U-Net models. Below we provide the multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d function which works.

source("R/_common.R")
source("R/dicom_plot.R")

U-Net the Example from man page ANTsRNet implementation.

source("R/multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d.R")

library(ANTsR)
library(ANTsRNet)
library(keras)

imageIDs <- c("r16", "r27", "r30", "r62", "r64", "r85")
trainingBatchSize <- length(imageIDs)

# Perform simple 3-tissue segmentation.

segmentationLabels <- c(1, 2, 3)
numberOfLabels <- length(segmentationLabels)
initialization <- paste0('KMeans[', numberOfLabels, ']')

Domain image.

(domainImage <- antsImageRead(getANTsRData(imageIDs[1])))
#> antsImage
#>   Pixel Type          : float 
#>   Components Per Pixel: 1 
#>   Dimensions          : 256x256 
#>   Voxel Spacing       : 1x1 
#>   Origin              : 0 0 
#>   Direction           : 1 0 0 1 
#>   Filename           : /Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/4.0/Resources/library/ANTsRCore/extdata/r16slice.jpg
X_train <- array(
  data = NA, dim = c(trainingBatchSize, dim(domainImage), 1)
)
Y_train <- array( 
  data = NA, dim = c(trainingBatchSize, dim(domainImage))
)

images <- list()
segmentations <- list()

for(i in seq_len(trainingBatchSize)) {
  cat("Processing image", imageIDs[i], "\n")
  image <- antsImageRead(getANTsRData(imageIDs[i]))
  mask <- getMask(image)
  segmentation <- atropos(image, mask, initialization)$segmentation

  X_train[i,,, 1] <- as.array(image)
  Y_train[i,,] <- as.array(segmentation)
}
#> Processing image r16 
#> Processing image r27 
#> Processing image r30 
#> Processing image r62 
#> Processing image r64 
#> Processing image r85
img_r16 <- X_train[1,,,1]
plot(as.raster(img_r16 / 256))

mask_r16 <- Y_train[1,,]
plot(as.raster(mask_r16 / 3))

cat("dim(X_train) = ", dim(X_train), "\n")
#> dim(X_train) =  6 256 256 1

Use multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d instead of multilabel_dice_coefficient

metric_multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d <-
  custom_metric(
    "multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d",
    multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d
  )

loss_dice <- function(y_true, y_pred) {
  -multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d(y_true, y_pred)
}
attr(loss_dice, "py_function_name") <- "multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d"

model %>% compile(
  loss = loss_dice,
  optimizer = optimizer_adam( lr = 0.0001 ),
  metrics = c(
    metric_multilabel_dice_coefficient_2d,
    metric_categorical_crossentropy
  )
)

Fit the model

track <- model %>% fit( 
  X_train, Y_train,
  epochs = 20, batch_size = 4, verbose = 1, shuffle = TRUE,
  callbacks = list(
    callback_model_checkpoint(
      "unetModelInterimWeights.h5",
      monitor = 'val_loss',
      save_best_only = TRUE
    ),
    callback_reduce_lr_on_plateau(
      monitor = "val_loss",
      factor = 0.1
    )
  ),
  validation_split = 0.2
)
plot(track)
#> `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

save_model_hdf5(model, filepath = 'unetModel.h5')
